definition.value: An alpha-amino acid that is glycine substituted at the alpha-position by a 2-hydroxyethyl group.
An iodothyronine compound having iodo substituents at the 3-, 3'-, 5- and 5'-positions.
A tyrosine derivative where the phenolic hydrogen of tyrosine is substituted by 4-hydroxyphenyl.
A bis(eta(5)-cyclopentadienyl)metal(II) having Fe(II) as the metal(II) species. The parent of the class of ferrocenes.
The glycosyl group formed from alpha-D-glucopyranose.

A D-glucosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of beta-D-glucose and, by extension, of a lower oligosaccharide having beta-D-glucose at the reducing end. The unsubstituted parent of the class of beta-D-glucosyl groups.
